(97, 1, '2021-01-10 20:27:19', '2021-01-10 20:27:19', '<!-- wp:cover {\"url\":\"http://localhost/unicorn/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/img-magic@2x.png\",\"id\":20,\"minHeight\":337,\"minHeightUnit\":\"px\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover has-background-dim\" style=\"background-image:url(http://localhost/unicorn/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/img-magic@2x.png);min-height:337px\"><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":50,\"width\":22,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\",\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<div id=\"cover-title\" class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"http://localhost/unicorn/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/ic-writer.svg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-50\" width=\"22\"/><figcaption>Myths and Legends</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"left\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">Once upon a time in a kingdom far-far-away in the lands of the<br>never-ending spring, a king sat in his golden throne and ruled his<br>kingdom in perfect harmony. A person can feel nothing but<br>exuberance at the sight of the magnificent castle in which the king<br>and his daughter lived. the majestic atmosphere of the woods<br>spread all around the castle, and last but not least - the<br>overwhelming beauty of the princess.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Heaven on Earth</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It was pure Heaven-on-Earth; there was nothing that could even<br>possibly attain the perfection of this place. The beauty of the forest<br>made it amazing, yet another thing made it imposing. In those<br>woods lived creatures of time unknown and one ofthem was the<br>most precious of them all… and was hunted for centuries for its<br>magical horn - the beast known as a unicorn.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One day a rumor started spreading. Someone saw a white creature<br>with the looks ofa horse, yet having a beautiful horn… and<br>suddenly all men grabbed their knives and spears, their bloodlust<br>and fierceness. The hunt had begun.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While the king\'s men were all setting torches on fire and sharpening<br>their tools, the young princess was at her chamber, brushing her<br>beautiful silky blond hair. She was the purest maiden in the whole<br>kingdom with a heart as tender as a rose and a soul as clean as the<br>water from the Fountain onouth in the woods. She had an<br>adventurous spirit and that day she decided to take a walk in the<br>surrounding forests. Pushed by the desire to pick some fresh<br>flowers, she left the castle and headed towards the woods.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"center\",\"id\":22,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/unicorn/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/img-tears@2x.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-22\"/><figcaption>Premium unicorn tears</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With all beauty of the trees and flowers and the crystal cleanness of<br>the mineral springs she lost track of time and wandered around for<br>hours and hours and suddenly, she was very deep into the woods.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>\"Could it be tr...\"</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She started realizing that the woods were getting darker and darker<br>and the trees were losing their beauty, the grass was dead and<br>there were no animals around. She started getting scared and<br>remembered a story heard long ago from her nanny, a story about<br>the Dark Forest, deep inside the beautiful surrounding woods.<br>Everyone believed it was just a legend, that it wasn\'t a real place,<br>but right at that moment she was thinking it over.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Could it be tr…” she couldn’t even<br>finish her thought when tree branches<br>started grabbing her legs and arms and<br>taking her deeper and deeper into the<br>forest…</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As approaching, it saw the<br>purity of the girl in front of<br>him and slowly began to trust<br>that innocent maid.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The creature was stepping lightly onto the grass, slowly moving<br>between the trees, heading towards the little glade where she was<br>lying unconsciously. As approaching, it saw the purity of the girl in<br>front of him and slowly began to trust that innocent maid.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the unicorn got to her, he bent his neck down and looked at<br>her beautiful face and slowly lied down next to her. After a while<br>she woke up and firstly got a little scared, yet after looking at its<br>harmless black eyes, she felt safe. Then the white beast stood up<br>and let her get on its back and they both headed towards the castle.<br>The princess was charmed by that creature\'s innocence and<br>nobility, by its graceful movements between the trees and its gentle<br>steps on the grass — pure harmony.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When they reached the castle and went inside the stone walls all of<br>a sudden, a lot of armed people surrounded them and the unicorn<br>started neighing and moving abruptly. The princess got down on<br>the ground and started screaming and telling the men that this<br>creature saved her life and brought her back to the castle. When<br>the king came, she explained him everything that happened and he,<br>while crying, told her that everyone had gotten worried about her.<br>He hugged his precious daughter and looked at the terrified beast.<br>Not until then he did realize that the unicorn is the purest and the<br>most innocent creatures ofthem all.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Sacred Animal</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During the feast that night, it was pronounced that the unicorn is a<br>sacred animal and it was forbidden hunting it. After saving the<br>young princess, the beast left the castle and never got back. No one<br>ever saw it again, but now all men knew the truth about the<br>unicorn.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is said that the king’s daughter met the unicorn again, yet that is a<br>different story….</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[wpb_popular_tags]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"textAlign\":\"center\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"has-text-align-center\">More magic</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:group -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\"><!-- wp:latest-posts {\"postsToShow\":1,\"displayPostContent\":true,\"displayPostDate\":true,\"displayFeaturedImage\":true,\"featuredImageAlign\":\"left\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:tag-cloud /--></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The Legend of the Unicorn', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '83-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-01-10 20:27:19', '2021-01-10 20:27:19', '', 83, 'http://localhost/unicorn/2021/01/10/83-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
